  '/blog/pimples-after-tattoo',
  E'# Why You''re Getting Pimples After a Tattoo (And Nobody Is Talking About It)\n\nLet''s talk about something artists hear constantly… but almost nobody writes about.\n\nYou get tattooed.\nHealing seems normal.\nThen around day 3, 4, maybe 5…\n\nLittle bumps show up.\n\nTiny whiteheads.\nClogged pores around the tattoo.\nTexture that wasn''t there before.\n\nAnd the first thought is:\n\n"Did something go wrong?"\n\nMost of the time — no.\n\nWhat''s actually happening has more to do with the healing environment than the tattoo itself.\n\n---\n\n## Fresh Tattoos Are Not "Dry Skin"\n\nA tattoo isn''t just irritated skin.\n\nIt''s controlled trauma.\nThousands of micro punctures.\nInflammation.\nA compromised barrier trying to rebuild itself.\n\nYour body is pushing plasma.\nYour immune system is active.\nFollicles are stressed.\n\nThat environment matters.\n\nWhat you put on the skin — and what you seal over it — can either support healing or create congestion.\n\n---\n\n## The Real Cause of Post-Tattoo Pimples\n\nIn most cases, bumps form because pores get blocked during healing.\n\nNot infected. Not ruined.\n\nBlocked.\n\nThis usually happens from:\n\n- Heavy occlusive products\n- Over-application\n- Excess sweat trapped on the skin\n- Occlusion from coverings\n- Or a combination of all of it\n\nWhen follicles are clogged while the skin is inflamed, small pustules form. It''s a mechanical reaction — not a catastrophe.\n\nBut it freaks people out every time.\n\n---\n\n## Let''s Talk About Dermal Coverings — Honestly\n\nDermal coverings (second-skin style bandages) can be extremely helpful when used properly.\n\nThey protect from friction.\nThey reduce contamination.\nThey help manage plasma in early healing.\n\nBut here''s what matters:\n\nWhen applied correctly, the skin is completely cleaned and stripped of oils before the dermal goes on. No aftercare should be underneath it. The adhesive needs a clean surface to bond to.\n\nSo if bumps appear while using a dermal, it''s not because someone put balm under it.\n\nIt''s usually one of two things:\n\n1. Natural plasma and moisture pooling under the occlusive film\n2. A reaction to the adhesive system itself\n\nMost dermal coverings use medical-grade acrylic adhesives. Some people tolerate them perfectly.\n\nSome don''t.\n\nFresh, inflamed skin is far more reactive than normal skin.\n\nDermals are a tool. Not a universal solution.\n\n---\n\n## Where Aftercare Makes or Breaks Healing\n\nOnce the dermal is removed — or if one was never used — what you apply next becomes critical.\n\nMany tattoo balms rely heavily on dense waxes and thick occlusives. They sit on the surface and create a barrier.\n\nIn theory that sounds protective.\n\nIn practice, inflamed skin layered with heavy product can trap heat and moisture.\n\nAnd when product feels thick or greasy, people use too much.\n\nToo much product.\nToo much occlusion.\nToo little breathing room.\n\nCongestion follows.\n\n---\n\n## Texture Isn''t Cosmetic — It''s Functional\n\nConsistency matters more than marketing.\n\nThe ideal aftercare should:\n\n- Melt into the skin\n- Spread thin\n- Absorb quickly\n- Leave hydration without residue\n\nHealing skin doesn''t need to be sealed shut.\n\nIt needs balanced hydration.\n\n---\n\n## Why Blue Dream Budder Was Built Differently\n\nAfter 24 years of tattooing, I''ve watched clients blame their skin, their artist, or their ink when the issue was usually environmental.\n\nBlue Dream Budder was formulated around healing behavior — not shelf appeal.\n\nIt had to:\n\n- Absorb instead of sit\n- Hydrate without suffocating\n- Spread thin so people naturally use less\n- Support a clean healing environment with naturally antimicrobial botanical components\n- Help defend stressed skin from everyday environmental exposure with mild plant-based UV-supportive oils\n- Encourage optimal skin recovery by supporting barrier repair and healthy cell turnover\n- Smell clean without aggressive perfume\n\nThe goal isn''t just "moisturize it."\n\nThe goal is to create an environment where skin can rebuild itself efficiently.\n\nWe want the skin to thrive.\nTo regenerate cleanly.\nTo recover as fast and effectively as it''s biologically capable of — without being congested or chemically overwhelmed.\n\nThat''s the difference.\n\n---\n\n## Why We''re Giving It Away\n\nRight now, you can try Blue Dream Budder free — just cover shipping.\n\nIt''s not because we''re clearing inventory.\n\nIt''s because once someone feels the texture and sees how their skin responds, they don''t go back to heavy, pore-clogging balms.\n\nWe could spend thousands convincing you.\n\nOr we could let your skin decide.\n\nThis is the first time we''re pushing it beyond direct clients and word-of-mouth.\n\nIf it works the way it''s supposed to — you''ll be back.\n\n---\n\n## Claim Your Free Jar\n\n[👉 Click Here To Get Your Free Blue Dream Budder](/free-budder)'
